{"id":"tracebridge:K190543","k_number":"K190543","category":"nse","decision":"NSE","product_code":"FRN","device_class":"2","device_name":"ACME Cardiac Monitor Pro","submission_type":"1","decision_date":"2019-08-21","inferred_standard_areas":["biocompatibility","performance", "software"],"deficiency_tags":["missing_risk_analysis"],"text_content":"1. Risk Management File Missing: The submission lacks a complete ISO 14971 Risk Management File. Specifically, the FMEA does not address potential hazards related to electrical failures during continuous monitoring. \n2. Inadequate Software Documentation: The provided Software Requirements Specification (SRS) does not include specific traceability to the hazard analysis as required by IEC 62304. \n3. Clinical Evaluation: Substantial equivalence was not demonstrated due to significant differences in the predicate device's alarm algorithms compared to the subject device, with no bench testing provided to validate the new algorithms.","text_source":"extracted","source":{"fda_db_url":"https://www.accessdata.fda.gov/scripts/cdrh/cfdocs/cfpmn/pmn.cfm?ID=K190543","openfda_url":"https://api.fda.gov/device/510k.json?search=k_number:\"K190543\"","pdf_url":null},"ingested_at":"2026-05-02T16:26:27.761Z","schema_version":"1.0"}
